# UTF-8 code generation

- All newly generated or edited source files must be written in UTF-8.
- Do not introduce garbled text, mojibake, or broken Chinese characters in templates, comments, labels, or data.
- If a file is likely to be affected by encoding issues, rewrite it cleanly in UTF-8 instead of patching only part of the content.
- For Chinese UI text, verify the rendered source remains readable and consistent before finishing.
- When generating files in this project, prefer UTF-8 BOM for rule files and other files that are repeatedly misdetected by the editor.

# Examples

```ts
const title = 'MES生产批'
```

```ts
// Avoid broken text like: 乱码
```
